description: Returns a list of available database blueprints in Amazon Lightsail. A blueprint describes the major engine version of a database. You can use a blueprint ID to create a new database that runs a specific database engine.

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token to advance to the next page of results from your request. To get a page token, perform an initial GetRelationalDatabaseBlueprints request. If your results are paginated, the response will return a next page token that you can specify as the page token in a subsequent request.

nested_items.name: blueprints
nested_items.description: An object describing the result of your get relational database blueprints request.

nested_items.name: blueprintId
nested_items.description: The ID for the database blueprint.

nested_items.name: engine
nested_items.description: The database software of the database blueprint (for example, MySQL).

nested_items.name: engineVersion
nested_items.description: The database engine version for the database blueprint (for example, 5.7.23).

nested_items.name: engineDescription
nested_items.description: The description of the database engine for the database blueprint.

nested_items.name: engineVersionDescription
nested_items.description: The description of the database engine version for the database blueprint.

nested_items.name: isEngineDefault
nested_items.description: A Boolean value indicating whether the engine version is the default for the database blueprint.

nested_items.name: nextPageToken
nested_items.description: The token to advance to the next page of results from your request.
